      "root_cause": "login_log.user_id is a FK to users(id) with no ON DELETE CASCADE (table has no migration file — created directly in Supabase dashboard, drifted from repo schema). Any user who ever logged in has login_log rows, so a raw `supabase.from('users').delete()` throws a Postgres FK violation (23503), swallowed into a generic 500. The same delete call exists in merge/route.ts's second step, so a merge would move roles to keep_id successfully then fail to delete delete_id, leaving a roleless ghost account that read to the admin as 'role duplication'.",
